---
title: Cherry-Glazed Pork Chops with Roasted Brussels Sprouts & Garlic Mashed Potatoes
description: Think about your favorite food. Now think about with a cherry glaze. Yep, it probably just got better. Case in point: these juicy pork chops! They’re topped with a tangy sauce made with garlic, thyme, sherry vinegar, butter, and cherry jam, then served alongside roasted Brussels sprouts and roasted garlic mashed potatoes. It’s a dinner everyone’s bound to love cherry much!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cherry-glazed-pork-chops-29ed8e69.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cherry-glazed-pork-chops-62f29e34901197ae62029730-4d7fe25a.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cherry-glazed-pork-chops-62f29e34901197ae62029730
cuisine: North America
author: Sara Heilman
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 690 mg
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}. (TIP: Cover with a lid to bring to a boil more quickly.) Reserve 1 cup potato cooking liquid (1 1⁄2 cups for 4), then drain. Return potatoes to pot and cover to keep warm.

While potatoes cook, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Peel @garlic{3%cloves}; mince or grate one clove (two cloves for 4 servings; leave remaining garlic whole).

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Place whole garlic cloves in the center of a piece of #aluminum foil{}; drizzle with @cooking oil{} and season with salt and pepper. Close foil to create a packet and place on one corner of baking sheet.

Roast on top rack until Brussels sprouts are golden brown and tender and garlic is soft, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #plate{}. TIP: Wipe out any burned bits from pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add minced garlic and @dried thyme{1/4%tsp} (1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings); cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Remove pan from heat; stir in 1/4 cup @water{1/4%cup} (1⁄3 cup for 4), @sherry vinegar{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @cherry jam{1} and stir, scraping up any browned bits, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. TIP: If sauce doesn't thicken, return pan to medium-low heat.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

Add pork and its juices to pan; turn a few times to coat. Transfer pork to a #cutting board{}; tent with aluminum foil to keep warm.

Remove roasted garlic from foil and add to pot with potatoes along with @dried thyme{1/4%tsp} (1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings). Mash until smooth and creamy with a #potato masher{}(mash potatoes), adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Stir in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, Brussels sprouts, and mashed potatoes between plates. Spoon remaining pan sauce over pork. Serve.